'''John Gordon Armstrong''' (born 1935) was a New Zealand [[politician]] of the [[New Zealand National Party|National Party]].

==Member of Parliament==
{{NZ parlbox header|nolist=true}}
{{NZ parlbox|term=43rd|start=1990|end=1993|party=New Zealand National Party|electorate=[[New Plymouth (New Zealand electorate)|New Plymouth]]}}
{{NZ parlbox footer}}
He represented the electorate of [[New Plymouth (New Zealand electorate)|New Plymouth]] in [[New Zealand Parliament|Parliament]] from [[New Zealand general election, 1990|1990]] to [[New Zealand general election, 1993|1993]], when he was defeated by the previous [[New Zealand Labour Party|Labour]] MP, [[Harry Duynhoven]].

He is one of six one-term [[New Zealand National Party|National]] MPs who were elected in a swing against [[New Zealand Labour Party|Labour]] in the [[New Zealand general election, 1990|1990]] election.

He was born in Wanganui, and attended [[Wanganui Collegiate School]].

==References==
* ''1990 Parliamentary Candidates for the New Zealand National Party'' by John Stringer (New Zealand National Party, 1990)

