{{Orphan|date=March 2018}}
'''Elizabeth Anne Bingham''' [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] is a British [[businesswoman]] and president of R3, the industry body for restructuring professionals.
A managing partner at EY ([[Ernst and Young]]), she joined the firm in 1986 having previously worked at [[BDO Stoy Hayward]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Women in leadership|url=https://www.theguardian.com/women-in-leadership/2013/apr/15/profiles-liz-bingham|newspaper=Guardian}}</ref>
She is a leading campaigner for diversity in the workplace for which she has been named a [[Stonewall (charity)|Stonewall]] Role Model.<ref>{{cite web|title=Role models: being yourself. Sexual orientation and the workplace|url=http://www.stonewall.org.uk/documents/role_models_low_res.pdf|publisher=Stonewall}}</ref> She was appointed [[Officer of the Order of the British Empire]] (OBE) in the [[2015 New Year Honours]] for services to equality in the workplace.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=61092|supp=y|page=N11|date=31 December 2014}}</ref><ref>[https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/391413/New_Year_Honours_List_2015.pdf 2015 New Year Honours List] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150102104907/https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/391413/New_Year_Honours_List_2015.pdf |date=2015-01-02 }}</ref>
==Awards== She has an Honorary Doctorate of Business Administration from [[BPP University]] <ref>{{cite web|title=BPP honours three outstanding women|url=http://www.lawandmore.co.uk/legal-news/bpp-honours-three-outstanding-women-in-law-journalism-and-business/|publisher=Law and More}}</ref>
Other awards she has received include: * 2012 award for achievement from Women in Banking & Finance * 2012 ranked 31 in the World Pride Power List of influential LGBT people worldwide * 2013 ranked 27 by Accountancy Age in the Financial Power List * 2013 named in the BBC Radio 4 Woman's Hour 100 Power List <ref>{{cite web|title=The Power List 2013|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b007qlvb/features/power-list-100|publisher=BBC Radio 4 Woman's Hour}}</ref> * 2013 one of Cranfield's 100 Women to Watch list. * 2014 ranked 18 in the FT Top 50 Outstanding in Business List.
In April 2014, she was a judge in the BBC Woman's Hour power list 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Woman's Hour Power List 2014 – the panel|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b007qlvb/features/power-list-panel-2014|publisher=BBC Radio 4}}</ref>
