'''Pauper apprentices''' in [[England]] and [[Wales]] were the children of [[Pauperism|pauper]]s who were bound out by the local parish overseers and churchwardens. Some had to travel long distances to serve in the factories of the [[industrial revolution]], but the majority served their terms within a few miles of their homes.
